This Starbucks is... fine. It's a Starbucks. It feels somewhat surprising that one of only two Starbucks on the U Street Corridor is so small & cramped - there's almost no indoor seating - but c'est la vie. The shop is clean, the baristas are always surprisingly friendly, especially for such a busy location, & their patio is tops for midday people-watching. Importantly, it's next to two key bus stops (the S buses up & down 16th, & the 90 buses back & forth 14th), which makes it a perfect caffeine pit stop on your way to or from the area.
